!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

cold /kəʊld/

(colder,colds,coldest) 

1. ADJ Something that is cold has a very low temperature or a lower temperature than is normal or acceptable. 冷的 

例： Rinse the vegetables under cold running water. 用冷自来水冲洗蔬菜。 

例： He likes his tea neither too hot nor too cold. 他喜欢茶不太烫也不太凉。 

2. coldness N-UNCOUNT 冷 

例： She complained about the coldness of his hands. 她抱怨他的那双手冷冰冰的。 

3. ADJ If it is cold , or if a place is cold , the temperature of the air is very low. 寒冷的 

例： It was bitterly cold. 天气冷得刺骨。 

例： The house is cold because I can't afford to turn the heat on. 屋子冷冰冰的，因为我开不起暖气。 

4. coldness N-UNCOUNT 寒冷 

例： Within a quarter of an hour, the coldness of the night had gone. 一刻钟之内，夜晚的寒冷就消退了。 

5. ADJ If you are cold , your body is at an unpleasantly low temperature. 感觉冷的 

例： I was freezing cold. 我快冻僵了。 

6. ADJ Cold colours or cold light give an impression of coldness. (颜色或灯光) 冷的 

例： Generally, warm colours advance in painting and cold colours recede. 一般来说，先上暖色调油漆，再上冷色调油漆。 

7. ADJ A cold person does not show much emotion, especially affection, and therefore seems unfriendly and unsympathetic. If someone's voice is cold , they speak in an unfriendly, unsympathetic way. 冷漠的; 不友好的 [表不满] 

例： What a cold, unfeeling woman she was. 她是一个多么冷漠无情的女人啊。 

8. coldly ADV 冷漠地; 不友好地 

例： 'I'll see you in the morning,' Hugh said coldly. “我会在早上见你，”休冷冷地说。 

9. N-UNCOUNT Cold weather or low temperatures can be referred to as the cold . (天气或气温的) 寒冷 [also 'the' N] 

例： He must have come inside to get out of the cold. 他肯定进来避过寒。 

10. in cold blood→see blood 

11. to get cold feet→see foot 

12. to blow hot and cold→see hot 

13. to pour cold water on something→see water 

14. N-COUNT If you have a cold , you have a mild, very common illness which makes you sneeze a lot and gives you a sore throat or a cough. 感冒 

例： I had a pretty bad cold. 我得了很重的感冒。 

15. PHRASE If you catch cold , or catch a cold , you become ill with a cold. 患感冒 

例： Let's dry our hair so we don't catch cold. 我们把头发弄干吧，省得患感冒。 

16. PHRASE If someone is out cold , they are unconscious or sleeping very heavily. 失去知觉的; 沉睡的 

例： She was out cold but still breathing. 她失去了知觉，但还在呼吸。

